Title: Ironman Prep: The Big Day!
WorkoutDescription: THE BIG DAY! . SWIM (50'): Either OWS or long set in the pool. If OWS, try to swim for 8-10' followed by 1' breaks. If done in the pool, please do the following: 1000 WU easy 1:00, 1000 Free @ perceived IM pace 1:00, 1000 Pull @ perceived IM pace (try to match or better time from previous 1000) 1:00, 100 CD . BIKE (4-5 hours): During the long ride, try to keep the output at IM goal HR/Watts (High AeT). During hour 2 and hour 4 of the ride, for the entire hour, alternate between 5' @ an effort slightly above your IM goal HR/Watts, and 5' effort just below IM HR/Watts. . RUN (60-75'): Simulate running the course by focusing on run/walk techniques and using that IM shuffle form. If you have energy to run 75', go for it. Everything after that is overkill. Make sure you use race day nutrition
